  "format": "Sean and Amanda break down Luca Guadagnino's tennis love triangle, then Sean sits down with screenwriter Justin Kuritzkes.",
  "segments": [
    {
      "kind": "review",
      "heading": "‘Challengers’",
      "films": [
        {
          "title": "Challengers",
          "year": 2024,
          "note": "Luca Guadagnino's tennis love triangle, and the movie Sean and Amanda call their agreed-upon favorite of the year so far. Zendaya (reportedly paid $10 million) plays Tashi, a junior champion turned coach whose career-ending injury redirects her ambition into her husband Art (Mike Faist) and his old doubles partner Patrick (Josh O'Connor). The film jumps around 2006 to 2019, cutting between the three as tennis stands in for sex. They loved the Trent Reznor and Atticus Ross house-music score playing over dialogue, the class-and-money subtext, the food-and-consumption imagery (churros, a Dunkin' egg sandwich), and the ball- and racket-POV shots in the final match. Sean called it a four-and-a-half, Amanda a five as an experience; both compared its structure to Bull Durham and expect it to land on their year-end lists."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "interview",
      "heading": "Justin Kuritzkes on ‘Challengers’",
      "guest": "Justin Kuritzkes on",
      "films": [
        {
          "title": "Challengers",
          "year": 2024,
          "note": "The screenwriter's first script he felt good about, written on spec after the 2018 US Open final where Serena Williams was penalized for coaching from the box. He wasn't a tennis fan before the idea, then became an obsessive; watching lower-tier events pointed him to the Challenger Tour as a setting he hadn't seen on screen. Mirka Federer at Wimbledon 2019 shaped Tashi's coach role. Amy Pascal and Rachel O'Connor produced and sent it to Zendaya; the department heads came with Luca."
        },
        {
          "title": "Safe",
          "year": 1995,
          "note": "His pick for the last great thing he saw, a Todd Haynes rewatch. He singled out the terrifying dome and the mirror shot at the end."
        }
      ]
    }
